message.content:
cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG

This paper deals with the analysis and manipulation of images based on the distribution of pigments across the canvas. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of multispectral absorption and scattering coefficients to model the pigments suggests the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The algorithm used for efficient recovery of pigment structure may also involve machine learning (cs.LG) methods.
